title: Night of the Lizard
description: A giant lizard has been spotted in the subways and Jameson is willing to pay $1,000 to the photographer who gets the creature on film. Peter turns to his college professor, Dr. Curt Connors, for answers. But not the answers he expects.

title: The Spider Slayer
description: Norman Osborn hires Spencer Smythe to capture Spider-Man. Smythe releases his deadliest weapon, the Spider Slayer.

title: The Return of the Spider-Slayers
description: Spencer Smythe's son Alaster is hired by the Kingpin to get revenge on Spider-Man and everyone who had a hand in Spencer's death. He rebuilds the original Spider Slayer, along with two more.

title: Doctor Octopus: Armed and Dangerous
description: Doctor Otto Octavius, one of Peter's childhood teachers, gets revenge on the Hardy family for cutting off the funding for his research, by kidnapping Mrs. Hardy's daughter, Felicia.

title: The Menace of Mysterio
description: Spider-Man was seen robbing the Metropolitan Museum, while Peter Parker was home in bed. All of a sudden a supposedly new hero, Mysterio, arrives.

title: The Sting of the Scorpion
description: Jameson is becoming obsessed with destroying Spider-Man. So he hires a man named Mac Gargan to try out a new scorpion suit, made in the laboratories of Empire State University. But the mutation of the suit begins to turn Gargan into a monster.

title: Kraven the Hunter
description: Peter has a job interview at the Hardy Foundation Research Center. But his interviewer, Dr. Mariah Crawford, is visited by an old lover, Sergei Kravinoff aka Kraven the Hunter.

title: The Alien Costume: Part 1
description: John Jameson, Jameson's son, finds a strange black liquid while collecting a rock called Promethium X on the moon. The black liquid finds it's way to Spider-Man, giving him a new black suit and the Kingpin sends Rhino after the Promethium X.

title: The Alien Costume: Part 2
description: Spider-Man is becoming attached to his new suit. But Eddie Brock has framed Spider-Man for the Promethium X robbery. Alaster and Kingpin send Shocker after Eddie to dispose of him. Now, Spidey will begin to see what the suit is really worth.

title: The Alien Costume: Part 3
description: The symbiote takes over Eddie Brock to give birth to Venom. Now, Spidey must go up against the most dangerous enemy he's ever faced. One who is stronger, more skilled, undetected by his spider-sense, and knows Spidey's true identity.

title: The Hobgoblin: Part 1
description: Norman Osborn hires a psychopath, known as the Hobgoblin, to kill the Kingpin. But the Hobgoblin plans to use Osborn and Kingpin's rivalry to his own advantage.

title: The Hobgoblin: Part 2
description: The Hobgoblin takes over the Kingpin's empire. Now Osborn and the Kingpin plan to use Spider-Man to take the goblin down.

title: Day of the Chameleon
description: A secret organization, known as SHIELD, asks for Jameson's assistants in capturing a terrorist known as The Chameleon.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 1: The Insidious Six
description: Spider-Man is beginning to lose his special powers. To make things worse, Kingpin releases Chameleon, Mysterio, Shocker, Rhino, Scorpion, and Doctor Octopus from prison.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 2: Battle of the Insidious Six
description: Spider-Man begins to turn the Insidious Six against each other. But his powers are still giving him problems.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 3: Hydro-Man
description: Mary Jane's high school ex-boyfriend, Morrie Bench, comes back into her life with new superpowers to control water. He's hoping to win Mary Jane's heart back.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 4: The Mutant Agenda
description: Spider-Man seeks help from Prof. Xavier and his X-Men about the mystery behind his own mutation. Beast advises him to hear Herbert Landon's presentation for a cure on mutation. But unknown to everyone, Landon's new cure is actually meant to kill mutants instead.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 5: Mutants Revenge
description: Landon kidnaps Beast and plans to use him for his experiments. Wolverine believes that Spider-Man was involved in the kidnapping.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 6: Morbius
description: As Peter tries to find a cure for his new mutation, his fellow classmate believes it is part of Peter's assignment and is planning to steal it for himself.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 7: Enter the Punisher
description: Spider-Man ends up being chased a man known as the Punisher when he is accused of kidnapping Michael Morbius.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 8: Duel of the Hunters
description: Spider-Man has finally turned into a gigantic Man-Spider. To help him, Dr. Crawford contacts Kravin the Hunter. But will Kravin get to Man-Spider before the Punisher does?

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 11: Tablet of Time
description: The ancient Tablet of Time has been discovered and Dr. Conners has been assigned to study it. But Silvermane and Kingpin are both after it as well.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 12: Ravages of Time
description: Silvermane plans to use the Tablet of Time to make himself younger. He kidnaps Conners to study it before using it on himself. But Kingpin is determined to make sure that Silvermane fails.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 9: Blade the Vampire Hunter
description: With Man-Spider kept at bay, temporarily, Spider-Man now turns to helping Michael Morbius become human once more. But a vampire hunter named Blade is after Morbius as well.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 10: The Immortal Vampire
description: Spider-Man and Blade team up to stop Morbius from turning Felicia and the rest of the city into vampires.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 13: Shriek of the Vulture
description: Adrian Toomes finances Dr. Conners new lab for neogenics. But, unknown to everyone, Toomes is actually stealing peoples' youth to have enough strength to take down Norman Osborn, as The Vulture.

title: Neogenic Nightmare Chapter 14: The Final Nightmare
description: The Vulture takes Spider-Man's youth to become young again, but he also absorbs the mutating DNA of Man-Spider. The Scorpion also returns, desperate to become normal again.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 1: Doctor Strange
description: Now that Spider-Man is free from Man-Spider's curse, his new problem is finding Mary Jane, who has received a mysterious letter from her father.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 2: Make a Wish
description: Peter is beginning to give up. He's tired of Spider-Man being called a menace when he tries to help. But when he receives a letter from Spidey's #1 fan, Tina, he decides to give Spider-Man one last swing.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 3: Attack of the Octobot
description: Dr. Octopus has captured Spider-Man and erases his memory. Now, it's up to Tina to save him.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 4: Enter the Green Goblin
description: After an explosion at Oscorp Industries, Norman Osborn has gone missing. Soon after, a menace called the Green Goblin appears and starts kidnapping the chair members of Oscorp's board.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 5: The Rocket Racer
description: Robert, a former troublemaker, has been trying to help his mother with her business and her illness. But when a new gang, lead by Big-Wheel, threaten them, Robert takes matters into his own hands.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 6: Framed
description: When Peter Parker is framed for treason, the only help he has is from Matt Murdock, both as his lawyer and as the superhero Daredevil.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 7: The Man Without Fear
description: Satisfied that Spider-Man is on his side, Daredevil joins forces with him to clear Peter's name and bring the Kingpin to justice.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 8: The Ultimate Slayer
description: Alistair Smyth is planning on betraying the Kingpin. But when Kingpin finds out, he hires Landon to inject his mutation formula into Smythe. Now Smythe has become the Ultimate Spider Slayer.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 9: Tombstone
description: Tombstone, one of Silvermane's former henchmen, has returned and is threatening to ruin the life of childhood pal, Robbie, if he doesn't destroy the story that he's about to print about the Silvermane family.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 12: The Spot
description: After Tony Stark eliminates Dr. Ohn's research on dimensions, Ohn makes a deal with the Kingpin. After a malfunction in his new lab, Ohn is sucked into another dimension and becomes a powerful being, know as The Spot.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 10: Venom Returns
description: Baron Mordo is back. He is planning to steal Tony Stark's technology on dimensions so that he can bring the being known as Dormammu to Earth. But he will also need the help of Spider-Man's greatest enemy: Venom.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 11: Carnage
description: The Venom symbiote has produced a new symbiote, attaching itself to serial killer Cletus Kasady to give birth to Carnage. As Venom's replacement, Carnage helps Mordo with his plans. Now, Spider-Man must team up with Venom and Iron-Man.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 13: Goblin Wars
description: The Hobgoblin returns, this time with the time dilation accelerator. The Kingpin turns to Norman Osborn, who created the Hobgoblin, for help. But when the Green Goblin takes over, it's war.

title: Sins of the Fathers Chapter 14: The Turning Point
description: The Green Goblin has found out Spider-Man's true identity. Now he's after Mary Jane, Peter's girlfriend.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 1: Guilty
description: Robbie is framed for robbery, and only Spider-Man and Jameson believe that he's innocent. Can they find enough evidence to prove it before Robbie meets some old "friends" in prison?

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 2: The Cat
description: Doctor Octopus and Kingpin break Felicia's father, John Hardesky aka The Cat, from prison. As a boy, The Cat witnessed the creation of Captain America and knows the formula they used. Now Kingpin wants the information for himself.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 3: The Black Cat
description: A mysterious figure called The Black Cat appears in New York and asks for Spider-Man's help in freeing John Hardesky from the Kingpin.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 4: Return of Kraven
description: Spider-Man has been refusing to work with Black Cat because he doesn't want anyone close to him getting hurt anymore. Meanwhile, Kraven returns to New York to hunt down the Stalker, a creature he has been said to have created.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 5: Partners
description: Smythe kidnaps Black Cat and tells Spider-Man that he'll set her free if he finds Scorpion or the Vulture. Smythe is planning to help make Silvermane an adult again using the neogenics from the two of them.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 6: The Awakening
description: Debra Whitman finds Michael Morbius in hibernation, on an island off of New York City. Felicia, as Black Cat, asks for help from Blade's partner, Whistler, in finding a cure for Morbius' mutation.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 7: The Vampire Queen
description: Blade's mother, the Vampire Queen, has come to New York and is hoping to transformer everyone into vampires. To stop her, Blade, Black Cat, and Spider-Man will need Morbius' help.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 8: The Return of the Green Goblin
description: Harry has discovered that Peter is Spider-Man. Now the Green Goblin is beginning to haunt him.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 9: The Haunting of Mary Jane
description: Mary Jane has returned! And she has taken the starring role in an unfinished movie. But when an illusionist brings her father back and lures her into a trap, Spider-Man turns to Mysterio for help.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 10: Lizard King
description: Spider-Man has revealed his true identity to Mary Jane and has asked her to marry him. She accepts. But now, a band of lizard beings kidnap Dr. Conners and take him into the sewers, claiming him to be their father.

title: Partners in Danger Chapter 11: The Prowler
description: Hobie Brown has always wanted power. After he saves Kingpin's son, Kingpin offers him a new battle suit. Hobie soon takes on the name "The Prowler". But when Kingpin double-crosses him, Hobie turns to Spider-Man for help.

title: The Wedding
description: Peter and Mary Jane are finally getting married! But when Harry finds out, he breaks out of the mental institution, planning to crash the wedding with help from Smythe and Scorpion.

title: Six Forgotten Warriors Chapter 1
description: Aunt May finally tells Peter that his parents were Russian spies. To prove their innocence, Peter heads to Moscow to find answers. Meanwhile, former World War II scientists are beginning to disappear.

title: Six Forgotten Warriors Chapter 2: Unclaimed Legacy
description: The Kingpin reunites the Insidious Six to find information on a mysterious group called the Six Forgotten Warriors.

title: Six Forgotten Warriors Chapter 3: Secrets of the Six
description: The Six Forgotten Warriors are said to have 6 secret keys to unlock a dangerous weapon that could destroy the world.

title: Six Forgotten Warriors Chapter 4: The Six Fight Again
description: Five of the Forgotten Six reunite and team up with Spider-Man to stop the Kingpin from activating the Dooms Day Weapon. But during the process of activating it, Captain America and Red Skull are returned.

title: Six Forgotten Warriors Chapter 5: The Price of Heroism
description: Red Skull uses the Dooms Day Device to transport power into his son and transforms him into Electro. As Electro begins to absorb more power, he becomes even too powerful for his father to handle.

title: The Return of Hydro-Man: Part 1
description: While on their honeymoon, Peter and Mary Jane are interrupted by Morrie Bench. Still obsessed with making Mary Jane his other half, Morrie kidnaps her.

title: The Return of Hydro-Man: Part 2
description: Mary Jane has discovered that she, too, has Hydro-Man's powers. She and Spider-Man find out that Mary Jane is actually a clone of the real MJ.

title: Secret Wars, Chapter 1: Arrival
description: Madame Web brings Spider-Man to meet her master, The Beyonder, who is preparing to put Spider-Man to the ultimate test. He sends Dr. Octopus, Dr. Doom, Smythe, Red Skull, and the Lizard off to destroy a peaceful planet and leaves Spider-Man to save it with his own selective team.

title: Secret Wars, Chapter 2: The Gauntlet of the Red Skull
description: Spider-Man and his team plan to infiltrate the Red Skull's base, along with a group of freedom fighter from the destroyed planet.

title: Secret Wars, Chapter 3: Doom
description: Dr. Doom absorbs the Beyonder's power and uses it to fight off Spider-Man's team.

title: Spider Wars, Chapter 1: I Really, Really Hate Clones
description: The Beyonder sends Spider-Man into another reality where the world is in destruction from Spider-Carnage. Now Spidey has to team up with Spider-Men from other dimensions to stop him.

title: Spider Wars, Chapter 2: Farewell Spider-Man
description: Spider-Man chases Spider-Carnage through multiple dimensions as he tries to stop him from destroying the entire universe and all of the different dimensions with it.
